    "answer": "3",
    "original_question": "ⓐIf self-consciousness, which has long been considered an important issue in philosophy, is useful, it is either useful in itself or gives rise to something else that is useful. ⓑUpon closer examination, self-consciousness is not at all useful in itself. ⓒThis is because self-consciousness in itself only causes distress. ⓓIf self-consciousness gives rise to something else useful, the useful outcome brought about by self-consciousness exists either inside the mind or outside the mind. ⓔSelf-consciousness cannot give rise to anything useful outside the mind. ⓕIf self-consciousness could bring about something outside the mind, then there would have to be something outside the mind that self-consciousness could causally affect. However, ⓖeverything that self-consciousness can causally affect exists only within the mind. Furthermore, ⓗthere is nothing useful within the mind that self-consciousness brings about. ⓘWhat is useful within the mind ultimately does not differ from a good state of mind. ⓙFor such a state to arise, self-consciousness is not necessary. ⓚIf something can arise without the need for self-consciousness, then it cannot be said to be caused by self-consciousness. In the end, ⓛself-consciousness does not give rise to anything else useful. Therefore, ⓜself-consciousness is not useful at all. <question> Which of the following most appropriately analyzes the structure of the argument above? <choices> (in DOT) ① digraph G1 { c -> b; f -> e; g -> e; j -> i; k -> i; a -> l; b -> l; d -> l; e -> l; h -> l; i -> l; l -> m; } ② digraph G2 { c -> b; f -> e; g -> e; i -> h; j -> h; k -> h; a -> l; b -> l; d -> l; e -> l; h -> l; l -> m; } ③ digraph G3 { c -> b; f -> e; g -> e; i -> h; j -> h; k -> h; d -> l; e -> l; h -> l; a -> m; b -> m; l -> m; } ④ digraph G4 { i -> h; j -> h; k -> h; d -> l; e -> l; f -> l; g -> l; h -> l; c -> b; a -> m; b -> m; l -> m; } ⑤ digraph G5 { j -> i; k -> i; b -> a; c -> a; f -> e; g -> e; h -> l; i -> l; a -> m; d -> m; e -> m; l -> m; }",
