    "id": "2025_10",
    "year": "2025",
    "problem_idx": "10",
    "objective": "This question assesses the ability to find valid arguments regarding the evaluation of advertisements for '1+1 promotions' and the administrative measures of regulatory bodies.",
    "domain": "Norms",
    "category": "Argument Evaluation & Analysis",
    "answer": "3",
    "original_question": "Company P released product A on August 1, 2023. From August 1, 2023 to August 31, 2023, the product was sold at the fixed price of 15,000 won. Thereafter, without specifying any discount rate, the price was set at 14,500 won from September 1 to September 10, 2023; at 13,500 won from September 11 to September 20, 2023; and at 11,000 won from September 21 to September 30, 2023. From October 1, 2023, Company P advertised a ‘Buy 1 Get 1 Free’ promotion for product A for six months via newspapers and flyers, indicating the sale price of one unit as 15,000 won. On February 1, 2024, regulatory agency Q imposed a fine on Company P on the grounds that the ‘Buy 1 Get 1 Free’ advertisement violated [the Regulation]. Q’s reasoning was: “ⓐ Regardless of the method of sale, consumers consider themselves to be purchasing at a 50% discount compared to the previous transaction price, so the ‘Buy 1 Get 1 Free’ promotion is deemed a discount sale.” [Regulation] Article ○ (Discount Sales) ① When a business entity conducts a discount sale of goods, the discount rate shall be indicated, and the previous transaction price for the 30 days immediately preceding the start of advertising shall be stated. However, if the price changed continuously during those 30 days, the previous transaction price shall be either the lower of (i) the average price for the 30 days, or (ii) the average of the lowest and highest prices within that period. ② Notwithstanding Paragraph 1, where discount sales are conducted consecutively under different conditions, the previous transaction price during the 30 days prior to the first discount sale shall be stated. ③ In case of violation of Paragraph 1 or Article 2, a fine not exceeding 30 million won may be imposed. <question> Which of the following can be correctly inferred from the above? Select all correct statements from <statements>. <statements> (a) If the interpretation is that Company P’s act of indicating 15,000 won as the sale price is solely for the purpose of a giveaway because the discount rate for the ‘Buy 1 Get 1 Free’ promotion was not directly stated, this weakens ⓐ. (b) According to Q, Company P should have indicated the sale price of product A as 13,000 won. (c) If sales involving discounts without indicating the discount rate are also regarded as discount sales, then even if Company P’s ‘Buy 1 Get 1 Free’ event is acknowledged as a discount sale, the fact that Company P indicated 15,000 won as the sale price in this event does not violate [the Regulation]. <choices> ① (a) ② (b) ③ (a), (c) ④ (b), (c) ⑤ (a), (b), (c).",
    "statements": {
      "statement_1": "(a) If the interpretation is that Company P’s act of indicating 15,000 won as the sale price is solely for the purpose of a giveaway because the discount rate for the ‘Buy 1 Get 1 Free’ promotion was not directly stated, this weakens ⓐ.",
      "statement_2": "(b) According to Q, Company P should have indicated the sale price of product A as 13,000 won.",
      "statement_3": "(c) If sales involving discounts without indicating the discount rate are also regarded as discount sales, then even if Company P’s ‘Buy 1 Get 1 Free’ event is acknowledged as a discount sale, the fact that Company P indicated 15,000 won as the sale price in this event does not violate [the Regulation]."
    },
    "original_rationale": "The passage states that Company P advertised a ‘Buy 1 Get 1 Free’ promotion for product A starting October 1, 2023, and that regulatory agency Q imposed a fine on the grounds that this advertisement violated [the Regulation]. [The Regulation] stipulates the requirement to indicate the discount rate and the previous transaction price when a business entity conducts a discount sale.<Explanation for Each Statement> (a): If the interpretation is that Company P’s indication of 15,000 won as the sale price was solely for the purpose of a giveaway, as the discount rate was not directly stated for the ‘Buy 1 Get 1 Free’ event, then the event would be considered a giveaway rather than a discount sale. This weakens the claim that “the ‘Buy 1 Get 1 Free’ promotion is deemed a discount sale” (ⓐ). Thus, (a) is a correct inference.(b): According to Q, Company P’s ‘Buy 1 Get 1 Free’ event is considered a discount sale. In this case, under Article ○, Paragraph 1 of [the Regulation], the discount rate and the previous transaction price for the 30 days immediately prior to the advertisement must be indicated. Since Company P’s prices fluctuated during those 30 days, in accordance with the proviso of Article ○, Paragraph 1, the lower figure between (i) the average price for the 30 days (which is the average of 14,500 won, 13,500 won, and 11,000 won, thus 13,000 won) and (ii) the average of the lowest and highest prices (the average of 11,000 won and 14,500 won, thus 12,750 won) must be indicated as the previous transaction price. Consequently, Company P should have indicated the lower price, which is 12,700 won. Therefore, (b) is not a correct inference.(c): If sales involving discounts without indication of the discount rate are also regarded as discount sales, then P’s sales at 14,500 won (from September 1–10, 2023), at 13,500 won (from September 11–20, 2023), and at 11,000 won (from September 21–30, 2023) should all be considered discount sales. Thus, if P’s ‘Buy 1 Get 1 Free’ promotion is recognized as a discount sale, it falls under consecutive discount sales under different conditions. Therefore, under Article ○, Paragraph 2 of [the Regulation], the previous transaction price for the 30 days immediately before the first discount sale, which is 15,000 won, must be indicated as the sale price for A. Thus, (c) is a correct inference.Only (a) and (c) from the statements are correct inferences, so the answer is ③."
  },
